Ben Clymer put it well in a Hodinkee article: Ah, the 5970. Some call it the best watch Patek Philippe ever made. Some describe it as perfectly proportioned. field.name: web_description_long
field.data: A horological milestone: the Audemars Piguet 25718BA. Introduced in 1991, this timepiece distinguished itself as the worlds first self-winding tourbillon wristwatch to incorporate both a date display and a power reserve indicator. This technical achievement, combined with its avant-garde design language, cemented its place in haute horlogerie history. The 25718BA represents a pivotal moment for AP, demonstrating their commitment to pushing the boundaries of watchmaking complexity.

This particular Tiffany 5396 comes complete with original box and warranty and is in excellent condition.

field.name: web_description_long
field.data: Introduced in the 1980s during a period of revival for the brand under the stewardship of the Chaumet brothers and master watchmaker Daniel Roth, the Breguet Perpetual Calendar 3050BA is a watch that bridges the gap between classic design and modern functionality. Encased in a svelte 36mm 18k yellow gold case, it features the signature Breguet coin-edge pattern along the mid-casea cold-worked detail that speaks to the meticulous craftsmanship of the era. At just 8mm thick, the watch exudes an understated elegance, making it a perfect fit for formal occasions while still commanding attention with its intricate complications. The dial is a masterclass in balance and legibility, a hallmark of Breguets Classique line. Featuring a silver guilloche patterna hand-engraved technique that adds texture and depththe 3050BA displays its perpetual calendar functions with remarkable clarity. Four sub-dials gracefully present the leap year and month at 12 oclock, the day at 9 oclock, the date at 3 oclock, and a poetic moonphase at 6 oclock. Framing it all is a brushed chapter ring adorned with Roman numerals, complemented by the iconic blued Breguet hands that have become synonymous with the brands aesthetic. Its a layout that manages to pack a wealth of information into a compact space without ever feeling cluttered. field.name: web_description_long
field.data: The Patek Philippe Reference 96 was the first and perhaps most iconic Calatrava watch when it was released in the mid 1930s. This reference was produced for more than 40 years in yellow, white, and rose gold as well as platinum and steel. Over those four decades, as few as 1050 pink gold examples were made and even fewer with a pink dial like the example offered here. This watch comes with an archive noting the dial and remains in wonderful original condition with a clear hallmark on the side of the case at 9 oclock.

field.name: web_description_long
field.data: In the world of vintage Patek Philippe, it is almost always a great sign when a reference earns a nickname. Enter the Patek Philippe Tasti Tondi 1463. This reference earned its nickname from the decorated chronograph purchasers which emulate a circular painting or relief. This classic chronograph, offered here, is in wonderful original condition with a clean tachometer scale dial and yellow gold indices. The watch is fitted with a yellow gold Gay Freres bracelet and comes with an extract from the archives at Patek Philippe, noting an original production year of 1968 and subsequent sale in 1969.

field.name: web_description_long
field.data: Introduced in the late 1970s, the Audemars Piguet Reference 6005 is a close relative of the Royal Oak but with a few notable differences. This reference was designed by Jacqueline Dimier who explained the birth of the watch - The temptation to introduce quartz in the Royal Oak line was great, but the management was opposed to it and instead created a related line, ref. 6005, that was rectangular with bevelled edge. It had the same bracelet and suitable finishing, but to set itself apart, the screws were replaced by four studs.

field.name: web_description_long
field.data: It was during the winter of 1972 1973 that a few young watchmakers set about rediscovering openworking, undoubtedly aided and abetted by their elders. Georges Golays vision was ambitious, as the operation kicked off with a hundred examples of Calibre 2120. The first watch was delivered on November 31, 1973. A masterpiece of meticulous craftsmanship and fine detail, Model 5442 provided a complex stage-setting for its mechanism. Through the caseback, the openworked oscillating weight revealed the AP monogram, in a pattern that would inspire the weights of Calibres 2120, 2121 and 2120/2800 for decades. Five more timepieces were delivered in December and an average of 30 watches were produced annually until 1976. - AP Chronicles

field.name: web_description_long
field.data: Named after one of Audemars Piguets eponymous founders, the Jules Audemars is a stunning dress watch collection that typically features impressive complications in a bid to act as a vehicle demonstrating Audemars Piguets horological abilities as a modern watchmaking powerhouse and as an homage to Jules impressive watchmaker who specialized in such complications. As such, the Jump Hour Minute Repeater ref. 26151 that we have here sports the incredibly complex and immaculately finished manual-wind cal. 2907 movement with a beautifully labyrinthine architecture as viewable behind its sapphire crystal caseback. Featuring two eponymous complications, a jump hour function and a minute repeater, the ref. 26151 is an intriguing watch with both complications that profoundly impact its design. As a result of its jump hour display, it features a digital hour display at 12 oclock and one central minute hand, with a subdial at 6 oclock displaying the seconds. Furthermore, its minute repeater function is operated through the slider found on the ref. 26151s satin-brushed mid-case at 9 oclock. Made of platinum and measuring 43mm in diameter, the ref. 26151s round case features a flat polished bezel that sits atop its slightly wider case, which gives a level of visual depth to its construction. Featuring the same level of visual depth, the ref. 26151s incredibly well-executed jumping hour display sports an interesting guilloche pattern within its center and a contrasting concentrically satin-brushed chapter ring to house its black applied Arabic numeral minute-scale, which only adds to its level of visual depth. An incredibly impressive timepiece inside and out, the ref. 26151 is a heavy-hitting timepiece no matter what way you look at it, and our example is offered in outstanding condition with its Archive Papers from AP.
